cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with language representation learning in neural machine translation models. It could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it involves training classifiers on extracted features from NMT models. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as NMT models are a popular application of AI in natural language processing. The paper also involves analyzing the performance of NMT models, which could fall under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper could be categorized under cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) as it involves analyzing the quality of learned representations in NMT models, which could be seen as a form of image analysis.
